		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
Because judges attempt to dispense &quot;justice&quot;, which is not something that can be objectively measured in the same way that medicine can.  In the case of a doctor, a petient either recovers or dies, so you can objectively measure their performance.  In the case of the law, two reasonable people can have widely varying opinions on the correctness of the way a case is decided and the way the law is interpreted.  Just look at all the death penalty arguments.<br />
 <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
