<br />
Anyway, you are right that reasonable people can sometimes disagree on interpretation of the law. That's why in critical cases you should have more than one judge involved. <i>But you should have those judges that most judges judge to have the best legal brains. Not those judges that the president believes will best creatively rationalise to pander to his lobby groups.</i><br />
