The search for justice is the reason half the reason for the brain-dead decisions judges make.   Of course, they tend to just focus on &quot;justice&quot; for criminals rather than the rest of society.  It's why we can't execute the mentally retarded or men who are psychotic murderers but just happen to be 17 years and 364 days old at the time they commit their crimes.  It's why we are forced to let dangerous thugs serving life sentences out of prison for medical treatment.  True, judges do not dispense justice.  But they like to say it is a prime function of the legal system.
                  
